---
export interface Props {
  title?: string;
}

const {
  title = 'Why Alberta businesses work with us',
} = Astro.props;
---

<section class="bg-slate-950 py-20">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-6 max-w-4xl">
    <h2 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold text-white mb-10">
      {title}
    </h2>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-slate-400 leading-relaxed">
      
      <div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-medium mb-2">
          Local market understanding
        </h3>
        <p>
          We work exclusively with Alberta-based service and local businesses.
          This means demand analysis, channel selection, and financial logic
          are grounded in real regional conditions â€” not generic benchmarks.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-medium mb-2">
          Systems before traffic
        </h3>
        <p>
          We do not push ads or scale activity before understanding where
          customers drop off, how demand behaves, and whether the economics
          of acquisition actually make sense.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div>
        <h3 class="text-white font-medium mb-2">
          Financial-first thinking
        </h3>
        <p>
          Every recommendation is tied to margins, break-even logic, and
          operational reality. If scaling traffic would lose money,
          we will say so clearly.
        </p>
      </div>

      

    </div>
  </div>
</section>
